//@version=6
// INV047: a string literal broken at EOL inside an open call must not
// poison the lexer's bracket depth (NEWLINE suppression for the rest of
// the file) or the parser's parenDepth (synchronize resets it). The
// declarations AFTER the broken statement must still parse and resolve -
// no phantom "undefined variable" cascades. Only the records on the
// genuinely-broken opt-statement lines should appear - the in-call
// recovery (#46(b)) consumes the `group="X")` tail as the call's own
// torn continuation (its bracket balance goes negative), so it adds no
// shrapnel. The absence of the phantom cascades is locked by the corpus
// baseline (the carrier mangle fixtures are snapshotted).
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects error: line=13, message=/Missing enclosing character in the literal string/
// @expects error: line=14, message=/Missing enclosing character in the literal string/
// @expects error: line=14, message=/Expected "\]"/
indicator("INV047")
opt = input.string("A", "Location", ["Top right", "Top
left", "Middle right"],
group="X")
f(x, r) =>
    y = x + r
    y
filt = f(close, 2.0)
upward = 0.0
upward := filt > filt[1] ? nz(upward[1]) + 1 : 0.0
plot(upward)
